There are two dimensions to the sociology program goals. The first dimension involves teaching the skills of the sociology profession. The second dimension involves the application of those skills to public affairs through public sociology. The first goal of the sociology program is to develop the professional skills that support the sociological imagination. These include: Knowledge of how to use theory to conceptualize a problem and to select and organize relevant social facts. The ability to use social scientific research methods to address sociological questions.
